data.title: Operation Gladio document collection
data.meta_description: Operation Gladio document collection - Download as a PDF or view online for free
data.text: This document provides an overview and summaries of documents related to Operation Gladio, the covert anti-communist paramilitary organizations established in multiple NATO countries during the Cold War. It includes summaries of documents from meetings at the Yalta Conference dividing Europe between Western allies and the Soviet Union, agreements formalizing this division, US security briefings expressing concern about communist influence in Italy, directives establishing covert anti-communist operations, and military manuals used to train secret anti-communist forces. The document shows that Western governments sought to counter Soviet influence through both overt political means and covert paramilitary operations, establishing the ideological and strategic origins of Operation Gladio networks.
